ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='The git diff stat shows only 8 files changed in the latest commit, bu
t the `.doc-coverage.txt` showed 57 files changed in the PR. This might be becau
se the PR has multiple commits and I only looked at the latest commit. But I hav
e already read the key files from the working directory, so I have a good pictur
e.\n\nLet me now compile the review report. I need to be thorough and reference 
specific files and line numbers.\n\nKey issues to include:\n\n**Blocking:**\n1. 
`MessageEntity` unique index on `client_message_id` alone - should be composite 
with `conversation_id`\n2. `ImService.getMessages` returns `MessageEntity[]` dir
ectly - violates NestJS Service layer standard\n3. `ImController` returns TypeOR
M Entities directly in API responses - violates NestJS Controller/DTO standard\n
4. `SendMessageDto.client_message_id` is `@IsString()` (required) but `ImService
.sendMessage` treats it as optional with fallback `dto.client_message_id ?? uuid
v7()` - inconsistent contract\n\n**Major:**\n1. `im.yaml` OpenAPI contract has s
chema mismatches:\n   - `ConversationDto` has required `id` but API returns `con
versation_id`\n   - `MessageDto.type` enum missing `system`\n   - `MessageDto.se
nder_id` should be nullable\n2. No offline push notification implementation in I
M module (PRD v1-mvp.md line 163 explicitly requires it)\n3. `ChatPage` only han
dles text messages, no image support (PRD v1-mvp.md lines 155-157 require text a
nd image)\n4. `ChatPage` doesn\'t clear current conversation on dispose, risking
read receipts for wrong conversations\n5. `MatchListPage` class name and file pa
th are misleading (displays conversations, not matches)\n6. `getConversations` r
aw SQL `IN (?)` with array parameter is risky with mysql2 (though might work)\n7
. `ImSocketClient` lacks reconnection configuration\n\n**Minor:**\n1. `SwConvers
ationListItem` hardcodes `identifier: \'conversation_item\'`, making Maestro una
ble to distinguish individual items\n2. `ImBloc._onConversationUpdated` is empty
- no UI refresh on conversation updates\n3. `docs/modules/im.md` incorrectly lab
els `match_list_page.dart` as "Conversation List Page" without noting the naming
mismatch\n\nLet me also check one more thing about the `ImBloc` state management
- when `ImMessageReceived` is emitted but `conversationId` doesn\'t match `_curr
entConversationId`, it returns early without emitting any state. This is correct
behavior.\n\nAlso, I noticed `apps/mobile/lib/presentation/blocs/im/im_bloc.dart
` line 117:\n```dart\nemit(ImMessageSent(List.unmodifiable(_messages)));\n```\nW
hen a message is received, it emits `ImMessageSent`, not `ImMessageReceived`. Th
is is a naming issue but functionally fine.\n\nOne more issue: In `chat_page.dar
t`, the `_getMessagesFromState` method handles `ImMessageSending`, `ImMessageSen
t`, `ImMessageRead`, but if the state is `ImConnected` or `ImDisconnected`, it r
eturns empty list. What if the user loads messages, then the socket connects/dis
connects? The `ImBloc` doesn\'t preserve messages across connection state change
s. Actually, `ImConnected` and `ImDisconnected` are separate states that don\'t 
contain messages. If the socket connects after messages are loaded, the state be
comes `ImConnected`, and the UI would show a loading spinner because `_getMessag
esFromState` returns empty for `ImConnected`. This is a **Major** UX bug!\n\nWai
t, looking at `ImBloc._onConnect`:\n```dart\nemit(const ImConnected());\n```\nTh
is overwrites the current state. If the user had `ImMessagesLoaded` state and th
en connects socket, the state becomes `ImConnected`, and the chat page would sho
w a loading spinner instead of the loaded messages. This is definitely a **Block
ing** bug!\n\nSimilarly, `_onDisconnect` emits `ImDisconnected`, which also does
n\'t contain messages, so the UI would show a loading spinner.\n\nActually, let 
me re-read `chat_page.dart` builder:\n```dart\nif (state is ImMessagesLoaded ||\
n    state is ImMessageSending ||\n    state is ImMessageSent ||\n    state is I
mMessageRead) {\n  // show messages\n}\n// if state is ImError, show error\n// o
therwise show CircularProgressIndicator\n```\nSo if state is `ImConnected` or `I
mDisconnected`, it falls through to `CircularProgressIndicator`. This means ever
y time the socket connects or disconnects, the chat UI shows a loading spinner a
nd hides all messages. This is a serious UX regression.\n\nActually, when is `Im
ConnectRequested` fired? Looking at the PR, it\'s probably fired when entering t
he app. The `ChatPage` creates its own `ImBloc` via `BlocProvider` in `app.dart`
. So when the user navigates to `/chat`, a new `ImBloc` is created. But wait, do
es anything call `ImConnectRequested`? Looking at `ChatPage.initState`:\n```dart
\nfinal bloc = context.read<ImBloc>();\nbloc.setCurrentConversation(widget.conve
rsationId, widget.currentUserId);\nbloc.add(ImLoadMessages(conversationId: widge
t.conversationId));\n```\nThere\'s no `ImConnectRequested` event! So the socket 
is never connected when entering the chat page. This means messages can be loade
d via REST API, but sending messages via socket will fail because `_socketClient
` is null. This is a **Blocking** bug!\n\nWait, looking at `im_socket_client.dar
t`, `_socketClient` is created in `_onConnect`. If `_onConnect` is never called,
`_socketClient` is null. Then in `_onSendMessage`:\n```dart\n_socketClient?.send
Message(\n  event.conversationId,\n  event.content,\n  event.type,\n  event.clie
ntMessageId,\n);\n```\nThis uses `?.` so it won\'t crash, but the message will n
ever be sent. The UI would show "sending" forever. This is definitely **Blocking
**!\n\nSo we have two more Blocking issues:\n1. `ChatPage` never connects the so
cket - messages cannot be sent\n2. `ImBloc` connection states overwrite message 
states, causing UI to show loading spinner\n\nWait, maybe the socket connection 
is supposed to be managed at app level, not page level? Looking at `app.dart`, t
he `ImBloc` is created fresh for each `ChatPage`. There\'s no global `ImBloc`. S
o each chat page needs to connect its own socket. Or there should be a global `I
mBloc` that\'s connected when the app starts.\n\nActually, looking at the `Match
ListPage` (conversation list), it doesn\'t use `ImBloc` at all. It uses `Convers
ationListCubit`. So there\'s no socket connection management anywhere for IM.\n\
nThis is a significant architectural gap. The socket should probably be connecte
d when the user logs in, not when entering a chat page. But even if it\'s per-pa
ge, `ChatPage` doesn\'t call connect.\n\nHowever, I should be careful. Maybe the
connection is handled elsewhere or I\'m missing something. Let me check if there
\'s any other file that calls `ImConnectRequested`.',
    encrypted=None
)
